-- CFTC Can’t Use Emergency Powers on Oil Speculators, Reuters Says
-- B y   R u p e r t   R o w l i n g
-- 2012-05-10T11:04:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-10/cftc-can-t-use-emergency-powers-on-oil-speculators-reuters-says.html
The Commodity Futures Trading
Commission, the U.S. regulator, can’t currently use its
emergency authority to impose trading restrictions on
speculators in oil markets, Reuters  reported , citing
unidentified people familiar with a recent internal legal
analysis.  To contact the reporter on this story:
